<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When using view helpers that extend {{Zend_View_Helper_Placeholder_Container_Standalone}} (HeadMeta, HeadTitle, etc), calling methods that will proxy to the container class will fail when those methods are not public. Currently, there is only one non-public method in {{Zend_View_Helper_Placeholder_Container_Abstract}}, which is {{_getWhiteSpace()}}. This is used when specifying indentation in the {{toString()}} method, and will trigger a PHP warning on line 207 in {{Zend_View_Helper_Placeholder_Container_Standalone}}.</p>

<p>Either, the {{_getWhiteSpace()}} method should be made public and the references to it should be updated, or there should be a check in the proxy to discard calls to non-public methods.</p>

